devdoc.details: All contained functions are pure and thus marked internal to be inlined on consuming contracts at compile time for gas efficiency.
devdoc.title: FixidityLib

userdoc.notice: This library provides fixed point arithmetic with protection against overflow. All operations are done with uint256 and the operands must have been created with any of the newFrom* functions, which shift the comma digits() to the right and check for limits, or with wrap() which expects a number already in the internal representation of a fraction. When using this library be sure to use maxNewFixed() as the upper limit for creation of fixed point numbers.
